      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mechanical tension is the heavy lifting part, where you are putting a significant load on the muscle fibers, causing microscopic damage. Metabolic stress, on the other hand, is the \"burn\" you feel, which is the buildup of metabolites like lactate in the muscle. Both are crucial for hypertrophy, as the damage from tension signals the body to repair and grow, while the metabolic stress also triggers cellular swelling and growth pathways.",
